 <CENTER> <UL><FONT COLOR="#990000"><h1><i>From Stargazers to Starships</i></h1>
</p></FONT></UL>
 <UL>  <H3> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; by David P. Stern</H3></UL>
<FONT COLOR="#990000"><UL><h2><i>Welcome!</i></h2></UL></FONT>
<CENTER>
<TABLE WIDTH="550" BORDER="0"><TR><TD>

<TD>
You have reached the <B>home page</B> of a book-on-the-web, a coherent,<BR> self-contained <B>course at the high-school level</B>, also suitable <BR>for independent study, rich in history. <FONT COLOR="#990000"><B>A button at the end of each text<BR>file brings you back here.</B></FONT> Its <B>contents</B> (full list further below) cover:<P>
</TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<CENTER>
<TABLE WIDTH="650" BORDER="0"><TR><TD WIDTH=40></TD>
<TD>
<CENTER><TABLE WIDTH="580" BORDER="02">
<TR><TD BGCOLOR="FFFFDD"> <UL>&nbsp; &nbsp;
<li> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I. &nbsp <A HREF="Sastron.htm"><B>Astronomy of the Earth's motion in space.</B></A>
